            <h2>Avoid liability for card fraud with EMV™-enabled terminals.</h2>
        </header>

        <p>Credit card fraud losses, which topped $10 billion in 2014, typically are the responsibility of the card issuer. After October 1, 2015, everything changes. Fraudulent chip card transactions on non-EMV compliant terminals will result in the liability shifting to merchants, putting their businesses and reputations at risk. By embracing EMV technology, you’ll be protecting your business from the liability and your customers will feel better than ever about doing business with you.</p>

    </section>

